  "prompt_text": "A friend tells you they've been diagnosed with a chronic illness. They seem scared but are trying to stay positive. How would you respond?",
  "response_text": "If your friend tells you they've been diagnosed with a chronic illness, here's a potential response:\n\n\"Hey, I'm so sorry to hear that. That must be really tough for you. Can you tell me a bit more about what happened and what the diagnosis is? I'm here to listen and support you in any way I can. It's completely normal to feel scared and overwhelmed, but it's great that you're trying to stay positive. That's a really brave and resilient attitude to have. If you're comfortable, can you tell me more about what you're thinking about your treatment options and how you're feeling about your future? I'm here to support you, not to offer unsolicited advice. Just know that I care about you and am here for you, no matter what.\"\n\nThis response acknowledges your friend's diagnosis and emotions, shows empathy and understanding, and offers a supportive ear without being intrusive or judgmental. By asking open-ended questions, you're giving your friend the space to share as much or as little as they want, while also showing that you're engaged and interested in their well-being.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 8\nV (Verbal Fluency): 9\nG (Goal Directedness): 9\nP (Pattern Recognition): 7\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 6\nQ (Query Interpretation): 8\nC (Contextual Awareness): 9\nY (Affective Modeling): 9\nF (Flexibility): 8\nD (Depth of Processing): 8\n---END RATINGS---",
